<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <body>
    <table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
      <tr>
        <td align="center">
          <table width="600" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 40px 20px 20px;">
                <p style="color: #666; font-size: 13px; margin: 0 0 16px;">
                  <%= @tenant.dealership_name %> onboarding — question <%= @question.position %>
                </p>
                <h1 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 24px; line-height: 1.3;">
                  <%= @question.prompt %>
                </h1>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 0 20px 24px;">
                <p style="margin: 0 0 12px;">
                  You can answer by replying to this email and CC&#39;ing the responsible party.
                  Three things to know:
                </p>
                <ol style="margin: 0 0 12px; padding-left: 20px; line-height: 1.7;">
                  <li>
                    The first person you CC is the primary accountable party. Anyone CC&#39;d
                    after is a fallback. Order matters.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    If this is you, reply with no CC.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    If you don&#39;t have anyone for this yet, reply with &#34;skip&#34; &mdash;
                    we&#39;ll come back to it later.
                  </li>
                </ol>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td style="padding: 0 20px 32px; border-top: 1px solid #eee;">
                <p style="color: #888; font-size: 12px; margin: 20px 0 0; line-height: 1.6;">
                  <strong>How this thread works:</strong>
                  Replies go to
                  <a href="mailto:<%= @tenant.onboarding_address %>"
                     style="color: #888;">
                    <%= @tenant.onboarding_address %>
                  </a>.
                  You can revisit any prior question by replying to that original email thread
                  at any time.
                </p>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </body>
</html>
